  "prompt": "Fix this code:\n\nMerge overlapping or touching intervals correctly.\n\n```python\ndef merge_intervals(intervals):\n    def normalize(items):\n        cleaned = []\n        for start, end in items:\n            if start > end:\n                start, end = end, start\n            cleaned.append([start, end])\n        return cleaned\n\n    def should_merge(current, nxt):\n        return nxt[0] < current[1]\n\n    def merge_pair(current, nxt):\n        current[1] = nxt[1]\n        return current\n\n    def should_copy_current(current, nxt):\n        return nxt[0] == current[1]\n\n    if not intervals:\n        return []\n\n    intervals = normalize(intervals)\n    intervals.sort(key=lambda pair: pair[1])\n\n    merged = [intervals[0]]\n    index = 1\n    while index < len(intervals):\n        current = merged[-1]\n        nxt = intervals[index]\n\n        if should_merge(current, nxt):\n            merged[-1] = merge_pair(current, nxt)\n        elif should_copy_current(current, nxt):\n            merged.append(current)\n        else:\n            merged.append(nxt)\n\n        index += 1\n\n    if len(merged) > 1 and merged[0][0] > merged[-1][0]:\n        merged.reverse()\n\n    return merged\n```\n\nOnly return the code.",
